import hashlib

signature = program_input["signature"]
sign_bytes = bytes.fromhex(signature)

print('sign len: ', len(sign_bytes))
def make_r_s(sign_bytes):
    if len(sign_bytes) == 70 :
        print("len: ", len(sign_bytes))
        r = int.from_bytes(sign_bytes[4:36], 'big')
        print("r: ", r)
        s = int.from_bytes(sign_bytes[38:], 'big')
        print("s: ", s)
    else :
        print("len: ", len(sign_bytes))
        r = int.from_bytes(sign_bytes[5:37], 'big')
        print("r: ", r)
        s = int.from_bytes(sign_bytes[39:], 'big')
        print("s: ", s)
    return (r, s)


(r, s) = make_r_s(sign_bytes)

ids.r.low = r & ((1 << 128) - 1)
ids.r.high = r >> 128
ids.s.low = s & ((1 << 128) - 1)
ids.s.high = s >> 128

msg_bytes = program_input["data"]
msg_bytes = bytes(msg_bytes)
msg_hash = hashlib.sha256(msg_bytes).digest()
msg_hash_int = int.from_bytes(msg_hash, 'big')
ids.msg_hash.low = msg_hash_int & ((1 << 128) - 1)
ids.msg_hash.high = msg_hash_int >> 128
